      "description": "<p><strong>Max Ranks</strong>: 5</p><ul><li><p>A Bruised creature suffers a -1 penalty to all Strength, Dexterity &amp; Constitution based attack rolls and checks for each rank they have.</p></li><li><p>A Bruised creature takes +4 bonus damage from all sources of bludgeoning or earth damage for each rank they have, once per turn.</p></li><li><p>Creatures that are immune to bludgeoning or Earth damage are immune to this condition.</p></li><li><p>A creature who would gain a sixth (or more) ranks of the Bruised condition immediately becomes Staggered, ending the Bruised Condition.</p></li><li><p>A Creature can spend an Action to make a DC 15 Strength (Medicine) Check to end this condition by applying the appropriate amount of pressure to the wound.</p></li></ul>",
      "tint": "#ffffff",
